It took almost 20 minutes for our drink order to even be taken. Bartender served tables that came in after us but didn‚Äôt finish our drinks until after serving that table. This is an easy spot for us since it‚Äôs right in town but we won‚Äôt do lunch here again. Do dinner here, not lunch.

detailedReviews.author: Pat Riot
detailedReviews.text: We usually take out but, tonight we dined in right by the fire and enjoyed the first 30 minutes by ourselves. The hostess/server was a sweetheart and very attentive. The food as usual was awesome. Missed seeing Steve but, I see him all over town anyway. I‚Äôll be honest‚Ä¶ the ONLY reason we come into town is for our mail and our occasional dinner at Boondocks! If it wasn‚Äôt for that I wouldn‚Äôt step foot in this bankrupt, broken down, section 8 lowlife trailer park town!

detailedReviews.author: Lacey Saucier
detailedReviews.text: I quite enjoyed my meal at Boondocks. I ordered a classic poutine for an appetizer. The fries were fresh, the cheese was melty, and the gravy was thick (I would prefer a thinner gravy, but I think most people up here prefer the thick gravy). I ordered a crispy chicken house salad for the main meal. The chicken tenders were perfectly crispy on the outside, juicy and tender on the inside. I cut them up and enjoyed them in the salad. I liked the portions and think that the price was fair. I did not use the restroom, so I can't comment on that, but the restaurant was clean and cozy. The service was excellent and friendly. I even enjoyed looking around the gift shop. I'm glad I got there before the supper rush hit, though. It's bigger on the inside than it looks on the outside, but there was still a good sized line of people waiting to be seated.

detailedReviews.text: Prices were through the roof, and sadly the quality we got did not meet the $$ we paid.. I was definitely disappointed and probably won‚Äôt be going back sadly‚Ä¶ sorry.. food was good, just not the quality we should‚Äôve received for the price we were charged is all..

detailedReviews.text: Always enjoy when we go.

detailedReviews.author: Brandy Peabody
detailedReviews.text: Wasn't as good as I had remembered. Waitress was nice, nice atmosphere. Steak tip alferdo was not very good. Alferdo sauce needs work. What they called tips were thin charcoal cooked thin slices of beef. The two flavors did not mix well together. Spinach and artichoke dip with homemade chips was very good. Also had a tenderloin clam seafood platter. It was good except the fish on the platter that we assumed would be haddock was not and didn't taste that good. Will try again but not right off as we live an hour away and drove up there specifically to eat dinner.

detailedReviews.author: Ruth Ross
detailedReviews.text: The service was very good. But the food wasn't very good. First time there so who knows it might have just been a bad night.

detailedReviews.text: The steak tip salad is the best just sayn

detailedReviews.author: J B
detailedReviews.text: I'm from Boston Massachusetts and my stepson and his partner moved to this town recently. My husband and I decided to visit and we were looking for a local restaurant to have dinner with them while in the area. Gayle was our server and she was fantastic! We eat at many restaurants and she is probably the most attentive server we have had ever. We started with the bacon poutine because I grew up in Massachusetts and have never tried it, it did not disappoint. My husband got a cheeseburger with egg which he devoured. Stepson got the haddock burger which was fried fish on a bun he said it was delicious. His partner ordered the steak tips which he said we're cooked to perfection. I ordered the half rack of barbeque ribs which came with mashed and Cole slaw. The Cole slaw was the best I've eaten. The ribs were mostly too dry to eat so I only had a few bites. Gayle asked me if I wanted a box but I declined, the reason she is the best server ever is because she came back and asked me if the ribs were ok, I was honest but told her I was in no way dissatisfied, everything else was great and my belly was full. The next time I am in town I will definitely be returning to Boondocks!

detailedReviews.author: hilda lynch
detailedReviews.text: Very good food and excellent service!

detailedReviews.author: matt howes
detailedReviews.text: Not many places hand make a burger any more. This place does. Over all good experience and should be 5 stars but the service was a bit slow while still very good considering only 2 wait staff were on duty.. during the towns summer festival. I will return again to see if i can give them that fifth star.
